summary: An email from an FBI agent in New York to an unspecified recipient, notifying them that the FBI team, including AUSAs, flew into Los Angeles to conduct an interview for the Epstein investigation at the interviewee's attorney's office. The email apologizes for delayed notice due to the sender being out of the office.

persons.name: FBI New York
persons.context: Sender of the email, notifying about travel to Los Angeles to conduct an interview for the Epstein investigation.

events.title: FBI interview in Los Angeles
events.description: FBI team, including AUSAs, flew into Los Angeles to conduct an interview for the Epstein investigation at the interviewee's attorney's office.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively conducting interviews for the Epstein investigation as of November 2019.
The interview took place in Los Angeles at the interviewee's attorney's office.
The FBI team included Assistant U.S. Attorneys (AUSAs) who traveled for the interview.
The email sender apologized for delayed notice due to being out of the office.
